==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stroma
<hw>Stro"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Stromata</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a bed covering, Gr.
<?/ a couch or bed.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>The connective tissue or supporting framework of an organ; <as>as,
the <ex>stroma</ex> of the kidney</as>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
spongy, colorless framework of a red blood corpuscle or other
cell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A layer or mass of cellular
tissue, especially that part of the thallus of certain fungi which
incloses the perithecia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stromatic</ent>⟦br⟧
